<https://doi.org/10.48723/f2xa-4005> <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#keyword> "Myelodysplastiskt syndrom"@sv, "Myelodysplastic Syndromes"@en, "myelodysplastiska syndrom"@sv, "Myelodysplastic syndromes"@en, "MDS-RS"@sv, "MDS-RS"@en, "SF3B1"@sv, "SF3B1"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__171.
_:b0__171 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/9c982fa9bcbdca5ad5d1befccb90371a>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.48723/f2xa-4005> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#qualifiedAttribution> _:b0__1952.
_:b0__1952 <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#hadRole> <http://inspire.ec.europa.eu/metadata-codelist/ResponsiblePartyRole/principalInvestigator>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#agent> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/c86274fd947a0e35e080a9d637a64b16>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Attribution>.
<https://doi.org/10.48723/f2xa-4005> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/accessRights> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/access-right/NON_PUBLIC>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/language> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002973>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Syftet med denna datainsamling var att bedöma flera parametrar om hur benmärgen hos MDS-RS-patienter skiljer sig från den hos friska donatorer. Denna datauppsättning består av semikvantitativ 10-plex TMT-proteomikanalys av FACS-separerade benmärgsceller erhållna från 3 friska benmärgsdonatorer och 3 MDS-RS-patienter. Se den engelska beskrivningen för mer information.\n\nDatasetet består av följande:\n\n- Processed data and analysis.xlsx (2.63 MB)\n- Variable_list_Processed_data_and_analysis.xlsx (23 KB)\n- Readme for raw data .zip file.txt (562 bytes)\n- Readme for Processed data.xlsx file (1.07 KB)\n- 13553_STD_EAEHPM1_10_TMT10_HiRIEF_3-10pH_20210504_07.15.zip (7.68 GB)"@sv, "This dataset consists of semi-quantitative 10-plex TMT proteomics analysis of FACS-separated bone marrow cells obtained from 3 healthy bone marrow donors and 3 MDS-RS patients. The objective of this data collection was to assess several parameters on how the bone marrow of MDS-RS patients differs from that of healthy donors. The samples included in this analyses were 3 samples of sorted GPA+ erythroblasts pooled from 5 healthy donors (2+2+1) and 3 samples of sorted GPA+ erythroblasts plus 3 samples of purified ring sideroblats from 3 MDS-RS patients.\n\nThis dataset includes the raw mass spectra, QC and processed results.\n \nProcessing: In short, FACS-separated samples were snap frozen in liquid nitrogen. Cell pellets were lysed with 4 % SDS lysis buffer and prepared for mass spectrometry using a modified version of the SP3 protein clean up and digestion protocol published by Moggridge S. et al 2018.\n\nThe following files are included in the dataset:\n\n- Processed data and analysis.xlsx (2.63 MB)\n- Variable_list_Processed_data_and_analysis.xlsx (23 KB)\n- Readme for raw data .zip file.txt (562 bytes)\n- Readme for Processed data.xlsx file (1.07 KB)\n- 13553_STD_EAEHPM1_10_TMT10_HiRIEF_3-10pH_20210504_07.15.zip (7.68 GB)"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#contactPoint> <https://admin.dataportal.se/store/818/resource/e455abbcd2b99eb4e8310f9a525bafb5>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#distribution> <https://doi.org/10.48723/f2xa-4005#distribution>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued> "2023-10-19T13:50:17.530755Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#landingPage> <https://doi.org/10.48723/f2xa-4005>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/modified> "2026-03-19T12:07:42.174815Z"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "TMT proteomikanalys av erytroblaster från friska donatorer och erytroblaster/ringsideroblaster från patienter med MDS-RS"@sv, "TMT proteomics of erythroblasts from healthy donors and erythroblasts/ring sideroblasts from MDS-RS patients"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#theme> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/data-theme/HEAL>;
    a <http://www.w3.org/ns/dcat#Dataset>
}

<feed> <https://w3id.org/tree#member> <#b52c79ddf39f00683bcfe3dc130ebf53>.
