    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/publisher> <http://dataportal.se/organisation/SE2021002817>;
    <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Green Chromatic Index (GCI) also known as Green Chromatic Coordinate (GCC) is a measure of the greenness of vegetation.  It is calculated from daily averaged RGB (Red, Green, Blue) composites values of digital images captured by PhenoCams.\nSvartberget Research Station (2022). Phenocam - Green Chromatic Coordinates (GCC) Composite Image Mean Values from Svartberget Experimental Forest, Mast 70m Phenocam 01, 2019-05-06–2019-12-31 [Data set]. Swedish Infrastructure for Ecosystem Science (SITES). https://hdl.handle.net/11676.1/TykoE43qFDjUQfn1x7mX2k6z"@en;
